  "description": [
    "A Proud Job By Father Gallagher Dear Mom You remember when 1 1 get out of school ami wed go out on those Navy ships on visiting days ami you always remarked how clean and spotless everything was Well since I came in the Navy Ive found out who keeps em clean The Navy man who joined up with stars in his eves and visions of himself manning a gun on a pitching deck of a warship may sometimes find it disillusioning that his present daily chore is no more than sweeping out a barracks or swabbing down the deck of a head It is just plain work and not very glamorous work But the reason behind his be ing in a military organization in peacetime doing only routine and apparently menial jobs is that we could wake up any day into a changed world wherein the only defense and salvation of our country would lie in the fact that trained and disciplined men were in readiness for immediate assignment to combat jobs much more deadly than pushing a swab halfheartedly Labor Day in the week ahead is a holiday set aside for the national recognition of the dig P"
